sources of datasets - 2010 to 2024

1. India Meteorological Department (IMD) - https://mausam.imd.gov.in/   : To get district wise data

2. Open Government Data (OGD) Platform India - https://www.data.gov.in/catalog/rainfall-india : To get data, verify data

3. Indiastat - Indiastat.com : To collect some state data

4. Some state level dashbboard - To get the data which not find properly and to verify details


Data divided as - 

Kharif: June-September
Rabi: October-March
Zaid: April-May





Formula and calculations - 




1 . Climate Score=1−(Temp Difference+Rain Difference​)/2

    Where 
    Temp Difference=(District Temp − Crop Ideal Temp​)/Temp Range
    Rain Difference=(District Rain − Crop Ideal Rain)/Rain Range

    Where
    Temp Range = max temp - min temp (among all crops in that season)
    Rain Range = max rain - min rain

    ClimateScore% = ClimateScore  × 100


2.  Soil Score = 1−(Ndiff ​+Pdiff ​+Kdiff​ +PHdiff​​)/4
     
    Where
    Ndiff​=​(Nuser​−Ncrop​)/Nrange
    Pdiff​=​(Puser​−Pcrop​)/Prange
    Kdiff​=​(Kuser​−Kcrop​)/Krange
    PHdiff​=​(PHuser​−PHcrop​)/PHrange
    
    Where 
    N_range, P_range, K_range, PH_range = max - min of each in crop dataset

    SoilScore% = SoilScore  × 100

3. SuccessRate = (ClimateScore × 0.6) + (SoilScore × 0.4)



Why 0.6 and 0.4 specifically?

0.6 + 0.4 = 1 → total weight = 100%

0.6 → 60% of the final score comes from climate - As climate is main factor in crops

0.4 → 40% comes from soil




Example calculations -

District climate & user soil:

District Temp (Kharif) = 31°C

District Rain (Kharif) = 700 mm

Soil N = 60, P = 35, K = 45, PH = 6.6

Crop ideal values (from crop.csv for Rice):

Crop Temp = 32°C

Crop Rain = 850 mm

Crop N = 90, P = 40, K = 60, PH = 6.8

Crop dataset ranges (for normalization):

Temp: min 29°C, max 33°C → range = 4°C

Rain: min 640 mm, max 850 mm → range = 210 mm

N: min 42, max 90 → range = 48

P: min 26, max 40 → range = 14

K: min 36, max 60 → range = 24

PH: min 6.5, max 6.8 → range = 0.3


Climate Score %: 0.518 * 100 ≈ 51.8%
Soil Score %:  0.4315 * 100 ≈ 43.15%
Success Rate = 0.6 * 0.518 + 0.4 * 0.4315 = 48.3%